{"questionId":"27002729","questionHtml":"<p>Find the area of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">R</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p>attempt to integrate <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>±</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></msubsup><mfenced><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></msubsup><mfenced><mrow><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></msubsup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></msubsup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>±</mo></math>&nbsp;correct integration. Condone incorrect or absent limits up to this point.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>attempt to substitute their limits into their integral and subtract&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>-</mo><msup><mi>sin</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>area&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award all corresponding marks as appropriate for finding the area between <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>Accept work done in degrees.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></msubsup><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></msubsup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;and&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></msubsup><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><msubsup><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></msubsup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>A1</strong></em> for correct integration. Condone incorrect or absent limits up to this point.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>attempt to substitute their limits into their integral and subtract (for both integrals)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;and&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>attempt to subtract the two integrals in either order (seen anywhere)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(</strong><strong>M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>3</mn></mfrac></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo> </mo><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;OR&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></msubsup><mi>cos</mi><mo> </mo><mi>x</mi><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><msubsup><mo>∫</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mfrac><mrow><mn>5</mn><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi></mrow><mn>6</mn></mfrac></msubsup><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>d</mo><mi>x</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced><mo> </mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>area&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A</strong><strong>1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Award all corresponding marks as appropriate for finding the area between <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math>.</p>\n<p>Accept work done in degrees.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27002729","referenceCode":"24M.1.SL.TZ1.5b","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the area of R.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumb